{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Importing data from legacy .dat files"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This notebook shows you how you can import data from a legacy dataset generated with the old `qcodes.data` dataset. These are typically generated with `qcodes.loops.Loop` or `qcodes.measure.Measure`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "from qcodes.dataset import (\n",
    "    import_dat_file,\n",
    "    initialise_or_create_database_at,\n",
    "    load_or_create_experiment,\n",
    "    plot_by_id,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# in case it was not there already\n",
    "initialise_or_create_database_at(\n",
    "    Path.cwd().parent / \"example_output\" / \"import_data.db\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "# put the old data in a new experiment\n",
    "exp = load_or_create_experiment(\"old_data_loading\", sample_name=\"no_sample\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "location2d = \"./data_2018_01_17/data_002_2D_test_15_43_14\"\n",
    "location1d = \"./data_2018_01_17/data_001_testsweep_15_42_57\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Starting experimental run with id: 1. \n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "run_ids = import_dat_file(location1d, exp=exp)\n",
    "axs, cbaxs = plot_by_id(run_ids[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Starting experimental run with id: 2. \n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "run_ids = import_dat_file(location2d, exp=exp)\n",
    "axs, cbaxs = plot_by_id(run_ids[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  }
